<hr>
<i>Posted by Lornick on 09-25-2003 08:09 PM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>You have completely the wrong attitude about LDoN shillingworth.  It's a win, win, win situation.  You need to exp anyway, so you might as well do it and earn augments for old armor, adventure points for new armor and spells, good sell loot (usually splits come to 100 - 300 plat a dungeon), and the occasional named mob item drop.  Not only that, but it beats the hell out of a static camp any day of the week.  Do you really find it fulfilling sitting around killing mobs as they spawn for hours on end with no risk or purpose?  With LDoN there is at least a purpose behind the dungeon, a goal if you will.  Everyone HAS to get off there butt and move through the dungeon.  Plus you get to deal with fun and new things like the traps, chests, and npc pets.  Plus on top of all that, each win you get applies toward improving your adventurer stone augment.  If you go into the dungeons with the attitude "god... 7 more missions until I can finally purchase XX item" of course it'll feel like work.  Just go in and have a good time, the rewards come before you know it.<!-- BEGIN TEMPLATE: postbit_signature -->
